headline: New credit scoring model for mortgages could help more people buy homes
summary: Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac will accept a credit scoring model for mortgage applications that captures rent and utility payments in credit history, a move that could help more borrowers qualify for home loans.

headline: 2 S&P 500 Stocks with Promising Prospects and 1 to Steer Clear Of
summary: While the S&P 500 (^GSPC) includes industry leaders, not every stock in the index is a winner. Some companies are past their prime, weighed down by poor execution, weak financials, or structural headwinds.
